istributor\r\nStephen - backpack extender idea\r\nClayton - look at a bunch of technology from a while ago, to see if they are interesting from the point of view of lightweight smart contracts (<a href=\"https://www.ethereum.org/\">Etherium</a>)\r\nKris - making <a href=\"http://www.awesomeshitclub.com/\">awesome shit club</a> a TV show\r\n\r\nIdeas Discussion\r\n-----------------\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.coitr.wtf/\">Coitr</a> Idea:\r\n\r\nBen - update on Coitr - summary: using monitors on the smartphone and a wearable device to monitor events in the bedroom to allow for improvement and entertainment\r\n-data to be encrypted\r\n-integrated with other commercial devices (Fitbit)\r\nMichael - any sexualized content can be difficult to get onto the Apple and Google Play, but particularly Apple\r\nBen - intends to market it as a more serious medical, self knowledge and self improvment perspective\r\nMichael - younger clientel will have less\r\nBen - maybe the shady side of the business would be interested\r\nKris - marketing it with a \'Netflix and Chill\' vibe might be a good way to keep it under the \'Disney\' family friendly aspects of Apple (and Google Play to a lesser degree)\r\nBen - I\'m interested in an IOS developer\r\nClayton - trust in the data and encrypting it, preventing de-anonymization of the data will be a key part of making the app legit\r\nBen - maybe giving away the app and selling the anonymized data will be the way to go\r\nMichael - like Kris mentioned, anticipating the difficulty of scaling the company without drawing negative attention from Apple and Google\r\nKris - MvP is social proof of tweeting results\r\nBen - maybe rebranding the app is an interesting idea\r\n\r\nKwan - online marketplace for cannabis\r\n-<a href=\"https://highgradeaid.com/\">highgradeaid.com</a>\r\nKwan - there are no good Canadian sites with good pictures, good content\r\n- most companies in Canada are focusing on their local area\r\n- true online companies at the moment, have been selling only what they are growing, so approximately five products\r\nBen - family member is interested in growing in Ontario\r\nKwan - applications are difficult at the moment so the best bet is to team up with existing supplier\r\n- would like to explore marketing opportunities with new markets and new technologies\r\nKris - looking at the website, it would be interesting to be able to see more data like strength and THC vs. CBD\r\nClayton - use bitcoin as an initial solution\r\nKwan - targetted clients will struggle with bitcoin\r\nStephen - incent them to use bitcoin by giving away product if they register their bitcoin account\r\nKris - there is a company <a href=\"https://bitpay.com/\">Bitpay</a> that does both bitcoin as well as credit cards, they might be interested\r\nClayton - B2B might be an interesting way to sidestep much of the legal risk.\r\nKwan - currently my customers are the end clients, and local, but people who are not local to cities with dispensaries are screwed. I want to address that market. Very often these remote people are older people, again bitcoin might be difficult for this target market.\r\nClayton - find other ways to distribute money - <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hawala\">Hawala</a> is an example of a side-network to the existing financial network\r\n\r\nStephen\'s Idea\r\nBackpack Extender\r\nStandard student and city workers have small comfortable backpacks that are uncomfortable to wear for longer stints with heavier weights.\r\nA backpack extender would be a frame that would clasp around the waist and clamp a standard backpack to that would allow the weight of the backpack to be carried on the waist instead of the shoulders.\r\nMichael - it\'s already been done:\r\n<a href=\"http://www.ventragear.com/shop/mainframe\">Ventra Mainframe</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.vertepac.com/\">Vertepac</a>\r\n\r\nClayton - <a href=\"http://ca.norton.com/spear-phishing-scam-not-sport/article\">Spear Fishing</a> explanation - getting to know your target for a specifically targeted phishing expedition.\r\n\r\nClayton idea - moving older tech to a new etherium platform\r\n\r\nduplicate commercial media - store it on a distributed encrypted network. Incentivize people to store it and allow access to it, and provide content with a Tor incentivizing protocol (they exist).\r\n\r\nanonymous contributor: <a href=\"https://put.io/\">put.io</a> allows direct download from a torrent-friendly server for 3.99 a month.\r\n\r\nKris \"I have never downloaded anything ever.\"\r\n\r\nKris Ideas - <a href=\"http://www.awesomeshitclub.com/\">awesome shit club</a>\r\nAwesome Shit Club - $50 contributions, people pitching business ideas and potentially winning the whole pot.\r\nLiberal Guilt Award - a side award invented on the spot at an event to provide a second place.\r\nKris would like to create a TV or Youtube show.\r\n<a href=\"http://original.livestream.com/awesomeshitclub\">livestream.com/awesomeshitclub</a> has old episodes (we think)\r\n\r\nKwan - maybe a show reviewing cannabis would work\r\n<a href=\"http://www.uvic.ca/research/centres/carbc/\">Carbc</a> - drug and alcohol research information and informatics','June 20, 2016','','publish','open','open','','june-20-2016','','','2016-06-27 20:49:09','2016-06-28 00:49:09','',0,'http://www.ideasmeetings.org/?p=123',0,'post','',0),(124,6,'2016-06-27 20:48:34','2016-06-28 00:48:34','Chair: Kris\r\n\r\nMinutes: Stephen\r\n\r\nAttendees:\r\n\r\nBen - Coitr idea (discussed previous meeting)\r\nMichael - from Barcelona, interested in the startup scene\r\nKwan - cannabis online marketplace and distributor\r\nStephen - backpack extender idea\r\nClayton - look at a bunch of technology from a while ago, to see if they are interesting from the point of view of lightweight smart contracts (<a href=\"https://www.ethereum.org/\">Etherium</a>)\r\nKris - making <a href=\"http://www.awesomeshitclub.com/\">awesome shit club</a> a TV show\r\n\r\nIdeas Discussion