bsite, it would be interesting to be able to see more data like strength and THC vs. CBD\r\nClayton - use bitcoin as an initial solution\r\nKwan - targetted clients will struggle with bitcoin\r\nStephen - incent them to use bitcoin by giving away product if they register their bitcoin account\r\nKris - there is a company <a href=\"https://bitpay.com/\">Bitpay</a> that does both bitcoin as well as credit cards, they might be interested\r\nClayton - B2B might be an interesting way to sidestep much of the legal risk.\r\nKwan - currently my customers are the end clients, and local, but people who are not local to cities with dispensaries are screwed. I want to address that market. Very often these remote people are older people, again bitcoin might be difficult for this target market.\r\nClayton - find other ways to distribute money - <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hawala\">Hawala</a> is an example of a side-network to the existing financial network\r\n\r\nStephen\'s Idea\r\nBackpack Extender\r\nStandard student and city workers have small comfortable backpacks that are uncomfortable to wear for longer stints with heavier weights.\r\nA backpack extender would be a frame that would clasp around the waist and clamp a standard backpack to that would allow the weight of the backpack to be carried on the waist instead of the shoulders.\r\nMichael - it\'s already been done:\r\n<a href=\"http://www.ventragear.com/shop/mainframe\">Ventra Mainframe</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.vertepac.com/\">Vertepac</a>\r\n\r\nClayton - <a href=\"http://ca.norton.com/spear-phishing-scam-not-sport/article\">Spear Fishing</a> explanation - getting to know your target for a specifically targeted phishing expedition.\r\n\r\nClayton idea - moving older tech to a new etherium platform\r\n\r\nduplicate commercial media - store it on a distributed encrypted network. Incentivize people to store it and allow access to it, and provide content with a Tor incentivizing protocol (they exist).\r\n\r\